race.comment: FINAL CALL (1) had been working towards his win last start, sitting on the speed and scoring by 0.8L. He turned in a strong figure from the front there and he can adopt similar tactics from a good draw this time around. Building a nice profile and can repeat the dose. REEL SERENITY (5) is better than she showed last time out when sitting handy with a very slow tempo being set. She was unable to sprint with them there, but with some more pace on offer in this event that should suit her much better albeit back in trip. Draws ideally and can bounce back to her best. BIRD ON A WIRE (3) steps up in trip today following a sound effort over 1650m at Belmont last time out. She looks to get a nice run on the map and ZJP's claim comes in handy. Can make her presence felt. SWEET SURRENDER (6) won under similar circumstances at this stage of the campaign last prep and has to be included. REGAL BOY (8) wasn't far away last start and is not out of this.
